.TH NEBULA-SHELL 1 "July 2026" "0.1.0" "NebulaShell Manual"
.SH NAME
nebula-shell \- Lightweight Wayland Widget Framework
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nebula-shell
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
NebulaShell is a lightweight, modular Wayland widget framework for Hyprland
and other wlroots-based compositors. It combines a fast Vala/GTK4 core
with Lua scripting and YAML configuration.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBrun\fR [\fIconfig.yaml\fR]
Run NebulaShell. Uses default config if no path given.
.TP
\fBinspect\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
Connect to a running NebulaShell instance via D-Bus and display widget info.
.TP
\fBschema\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
Generate JSON Schema for YAML editor intellisense.
.TP
\fBhelp\fR
Show help message with usage and examples.
.TP
\fBversion\fR
Show version information.
.SH INSPECT OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--id\fR \fI<id>\fR
Show widget by unique identifier.
.TP
\fB--class\fR \fI<class>\fR
Show widgets matching a CSS class.
.TP
\fB--type\fR \fI<type>\fR
Show widgets by GTK type (e.g. GtkBox, GtkLabel, GtkButton).
.TP
\fB--tree\fR
Show full GTK widget tree hierarchy.
.TP
\fB--json\fR
Output widget information in JSON format.
.TP
\fB--help\fR, \fB-h\fR
Show inspect help.
.SH SCHEMA OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--output\fR \fI<path>\fR
Write schema to file instead of stdout.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI/etc/nebula-shell/config.yaml\fR
System default configuration (read-only).
.TP
\fI~/.config/nebula-shell/config.yaml\fR
User configuration (overrides system).
.TP
\fI/etc/nebula-shell/events.lua\fR
System default event handlers.
.TP
\fI~/.config/nebula-shell/events.lua\fR
User event handlers (overrides system).
.TP
\fI/etc/nebula-shell/styles/style.css\fR
System default GTK styling.
.TP
\fI~/.config/nebula-shell/styles/style.css\fR
User styling overrides.
.TP
\fI/etc/nebula-shell/widgets/nebula/*.lua\fR
Built-in widget definitions.
.TP
\fI~/.config/nebula-shell/widgets/custom/*.lua\fR
User custom widget definitions.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
\fBnebula-shell run\fR
Run with default system configuration.
.TP
\fBnebula-shell run ~/myconfig.yaml\fR
Run with a custom configuration file.
.TP
\fBexport NEBULA_LOG=debug && nebula-shell run\fR
Run with debug logging enabled.
.TP
\fBnebula-shell inspect\fR
Show all running widgets with basic information.
.TP
\fBnebula-shell inspect --id main_bar\fR
Show details for a specific widget by ID.
.TP
\fBnebula-shell inspect --class button --json\fR
Show all buttons in JSON format.
.TP
\fBnebula-shell schema\fR
Print JSON Schema to stdout.
.TP
\fBnebula-shell schema --output ~/.config/nebula-shell/schema.json\fR
Write JSON Schema to user config directory.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBNEBULA_CONFIG\fR
Path to a custom configuration file. Overrides default config resolution.
.TP
\fBNEBULA_LOG\fR
Set log level: debug, info, warning, error. Default: info.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gtk4 (1),
.BR wayland (7),
.BR lua (1)
